    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p>This oddly lifelike statuette's turquoise gems sparkle brightly as it sits stoically on its perch atop a hide epaulette. At a paltry eight inches tall while hunched, the tiny sculpture appears as a stone gargoyle that's been petrified mid-screech.</p>\n<p>In truth, the statuette is quite literally a guardian angel, albeit an unusual one. Aesthetically similar to those found on churches and cathedrals, it remains utterly still until its wearer's life is seriously threatened—at which time it springs into action and attempts to safeguard its charge. Though, its loyalty comes with a price.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong style=\"color:#191813;font-style:italic\">Rule Clarification, Guardgoyle.</strong><span style=\"color:#191813;font-style:italic\"> Full rules for the guardgoyle can be found in @Compendium[ddd-beginner-baubles.items.NmVslULE8R37JgaI]{Guardgoyle}.</span></p>\n</blockquote>",
        "public": ""
